reviewText: This movie was a favorite of my daughter, we watched it over and over back in the 80's. The love that the nanny had for this child was so unconditional -- and her parentals could certainly not measure up, with their lack of involvement in this child's life.  Will always be a favorite.  Isabelle Rosalini magnificent!

reviewerName: Graham D. Lincoln "The Truth is Absolutely No...
reviewText: I have been looking for this movie, since I saw it on Cable a few years ago. Where I live, I cannot locate the film (even in rental stores).  Normally, I am not a big David Lynch fan--because, most of his films are dark, depressing, sick and leave you feeling emotionally drained or like your morals have been run through a cheese grater. However, with that preface, I would like to say that "Zelly and Me" is a wonderful movie! I was worried that it had been taken out of print, because it is so obscure.  This is one of those rare films that really impact you in a way you can barely describe....  It is very difficult to explain to someone why they should acquire this film--it is a typical Lynch flick, because it is somewhat depressing and slow...but, it is Brighter and (dare I say?) almost cheerful in small doses!  "Zelly and Me" does not really feel like a Lynch film, until the end is approaching (when you are too hooked to escape). It has been years, since I saw this great movie, and I still would very-much like to track Lynch down and tell him he cannot end the movie the way he did <Legal Disclaimer: This is a joke, folks>. You just sit there and stare at the TV, mumbling, "He can't do that.... This isn't right." You will find the movie disturbing (it's Lynch), but not in the usual way. "Zelly and Me" is what I would call "Profoundly Disturbing." The film makes you think....
summary: Ah, I Found it !  I've searched for this movie in stores....

reviewText: Isabella Rossellini is sublime in this incredible drama involving a Nanny's un-dying support and love for a troubled child, played FANTASICALLY by Alexandra Jones. This child will steal your heart.The scenes are dreamy...especially the wedding scene. SO BEAUTIFUL!David Lynch as a Love Interest cannot be missed! Really superb!!!I WISH I WISH I WISH This would come out on DVD...PLEEEEAAAASE..!
